{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyNTWco6WW5f9IffsiFhSYJ3"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# AstroPredict — Notebook 05  \n","## Interface-Style Inference Demonstration\n","\n","This notebook demonstrates how the trained AstroPredict models can be accessed and executed through an interface-style workflow designed to resemble programmatic or service-level usage.\n","\n","Using live NOAA GOES X-ray observations, the system first determines the current solar activity state. Because real-time solar magnetic field (SHARP) data is not available due to an inherent processing latency of approximately 24–48 hours, a scenario-based demonstration approach is employed. In this approach, a physically consistent historical SHARP magnetic field sequence corresponding to the detected activity state is retrieved from a prebuilt context library.\n","\n","The selected magnetic sequence is then passed to the trained LSTM and BiLSTM models to generate probabilistic flare risk estimates, along with an ensemble score. The notebook illustrates how live data ingestion, context-aware input preparation, and model inference can be composed into a structured, service-ready workflow.\n","\n","This notebook is intended solely for demonstration and system-integration illustration. It does not represent an operational API or a deployed real-time forecasting service.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"57GflkDrEWqj"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Imports & Setup\n","\n","This cell imports the required dependencies for executing the real-time inference demonstration, including model loading, live data retrieval, and visualization."],"metadata":{"id":"sGFiupk0NfKR"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"VksUzs86EKXh"},"outputs":[],"source":["import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import requests\n","import joblib\n","import tensorflow as tf\n","from datetime import datetime, timezone\n","import random\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Load Models & Context Library\n","\n","This cell mounts persistent storage and loads the trained LSTM, BiLSTM models, and the prebuilt SHARP context library required for inference.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"Q6AmQHgyNpM7"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')\n","\n","lstm_model = tf.keras.models.load_model(\n","    \"/content/drive/MyDrive/AstroPredict_Final/lstm_phase1_model.keras\"\n",")\n","\n","bilstm_model = tf.keras.models.load_model(\n","    \"/content/drive/MyDrive/AstroPredict_Final/bilstm_phase1_model.keras\"\n",")\n","\n","context_lib = joblib.load(\n","    \"/content/drive/MyDrive/AstroPredict_Final/sharp_context.pkl\"\n",")\n","\n","print(\"Models and context library loaded.\")\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"e92bu88cEjwC","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1765978109291,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":3571,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammed Asharudheen.A","userId":"07135212616055888141"}},"outputId":"85ff4da1-45b6-426e-80aa-198f1abdda3c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Drive already mounted at /content/drive; to attempt to forcibly remount, call drive.mount(\"/content/drive\", force_remount=True).\n","Models and context library loaded.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Live GOES X-ray Data Ingestion\n","\n","This cell retrieves the most recent GOES X-ray flux measurements from the NOAA public API using a fault-tolerant data fetch routine.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"zELJdOjtN0SO"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def fetch_goes_current_safe():\n","    GOES_URL = \"https://services.swpc.noaa.gov/json/goes/primary/xrays-1-day.json\"\n","    try:\n","        resp = requests.get(GOES_URL, timeout=10)\n","        data = resp.json()\n","        df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n","        df[\"time_tag\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"time_tag\"], utc=True)\n","        latest = df.iloc[-1]\n","        return df, float(latest[\"flux\"])\n","    except Exception as e:\n","        print(\"⚠️ GOES fetch failed:\", e)\n","        return None, np.nan\n","\n","goes_df, current_flux = fetch_goes_current_safe()\n","print(\"Current GOES Flux:\", current_flux)\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Y9V_M55LgGVE","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1765978176338,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":241,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammed Asharudheen.A","userId":"07135212616055888141"}},"outputId":"6c83a944-5d42-45e8-cd77-75ecb31f16e9"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Current GOES Flux: 8.112368732327013e-07\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Live X-ray Flux Visualization\n","\n","This cell visualizes recent GOES X-ray flux measurements to provide situational awareness of current solar activity.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"7pium-UsOTBM"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))\n","plt.plot(goes_df[\"time_tag\"].tail(120), goes_df[\"flux\"].tail(120))\n","plt.yscale(\"log\")\n","plt.axhline(1e-6, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", label=\"C-class threshold\")\n","plt.title(\"Live GOES X-ray Flux (Last 2 Hours)\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"UTC Time\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Flux (W/m²)\")\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.grid(True)\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":279},"id":"RnrlLNH_gJab","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1765978187849,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":887,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammed Asharudheen.A","userId":"07135212616055888141"}},"outputId":"c67d106c-7b94-4cec-dbbc-5743ae917795"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["This plot shows the recent evolution of solar soft X-ray flux measured by GOES over the last two hours.  \n","The dashed horizontal line marks the C-class activity threshold (10⁻⁶ W/m²). Values below this level indicate relatively quiet solar conditions, while sustained crossings above it indicate elevated activity associated with flare-capable regions.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"DqAA0XfWOpEr"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Solar Activity Classification\n","\n","This cell classifies the current solar state as QUIET or ACTIVE based on the latest GOES X-ray flux measurement.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"l-5KD6r7PFuc"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def classify_activity(flux):\n","    return \"QUIET\" if flux < 1e-6 else \"ACTIVE\"\n","\n","activity_state = classify_activity(current_flux)\n","print(\"Current Solar State:\", activity_state)\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"vxz9hIj9gNur","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1765978204385,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":9,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammed Asharudheen.A","userId":"07135212616055888141"}},"outputId":"78517459-3a2a-4a90-f630-9f435c0c34f7"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Current Solar State: QUIET\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Context-Aware SHARP Sequence Selection\n","\n","This cell selects a representative SHARP magnetic field sequence corresponding to the current solar activity state and prepares it for model inference.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"9gfmq6BUPuR3"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["sharp_window = random.choice(context_lib[activity_state])\n","sharp_input = np.expand_dims(sharp_window, axis=0)\n","\n","print(\"Selected SHARP sequence shape:\", sharp_input.shape)\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"U01u-WmGgRaN","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1765978219126,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":11,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammed Asharudheen.A","userId":"07135212616055888141"}},"outputId":"ddd9d4fc-8781-49ea-d8c5-3ec415480dab"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Selected SHARP sequence shape: (1, 30, 13)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Model Inference\n","\n","This cell performs inference using the trained LSTM and BiLSTM models and computes an ensemble probability for solar flare occurrence within the next 24 hours.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"-Wm5fsHGP-gN"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["lstm_prob = lstm_model.predict(sharp_input, verbose=0)[0][0]\n","bilstm_prob = bilstm_model.predict(sharp_input, verbose=0)[0][0]\n","\n","ensemble_prob = (lstm_prob + bilstm_prob) / 2\n","\n","print(f\"LSTM Probability: {lstm_prob:.3f}\")\n","print(f\"BiLSTM Probability: {bilstm_prob:.3f}\")\n","print(f\"Ensemble Probability: {ensemble_prob:.3f}\")\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"fUU6wbizgT7G","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1765978230232,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":627,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammed Asharudheen.A","userId":"07135212616055888141"}},"outputId":"eec9e6b6-c7ae-4720-9b37-8e6251e274b7"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["LSTM Probability: 0.649\n","BiLSTM Probability: 0.980\n","Ensemble Probability: 0.814\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Interpretation of Results\n","\n","• The X-ray data is fetched live from NOAA GOES satellites  \n","• The AI model does not see live magnetic data  \n","• Instead, it is shown a physically consistent magnetic scenario  \n","• This demonstrates how the trained system reacts under current solar conditions  \n","\n","This approach ensures:\n","✔ Scientific honesty  \n","✔ Real-time responsiveness  \n"],"metadata":{"id":"sex4V9hcjbYg"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Notebook Summary\n","\n","This notebook presents an interface-oriented demonstration of the AstroPredict inference pipeline, showing how trained models can be invoked in a structured, service-like workflow.\n","\n","Live GOES X-ray measurements are used to determine the current solar activity state, after which a context-matched historical SHARP magnetic field sequence is retrieved to compensate for the lack of real-time magnetogram availability. The retrieved sequence is passed to the trained LSTM and BiLSTM models to produce probabilistic flare risk estimates and an ensemble score.\n","\n","The notebook highlights how AstroPredict’s core inference logic can be packaged in a modular and reusable manner suitable for integration into external systems such as APIs, dashboards, or automated monitoring pipelines. It serves as a bridge between experimental notebooks and deployment-oriented system design.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"_6P7SWSEQhga"}}]}